{"type":"message","id":"d186ad9c","parentId":"c15dfc00","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:02:49.431Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 19:02 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Fix long-prompt-orchestrator for Real Usable Plans\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because it generates plans that are not executable by the main agent. Plans contain abstract task descriptions instead of actionable instructions.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent plan format (defective):\n```json\n{\n  \"task_01\": \"Which skills actually work and produce real results.\",\n  \"task_02\": \"Which skills only simulate functionality...\"\n}\n```\n\nRequired plan format (functional):\n```json\n{\n  \"task_01\": {\n    \"objective\": \"Inventory all skills in workspace\",\n    \"execution_mode\": \"main\",\n    \"action_type\": \"exec\",\n    \"action_instructions\": \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills -type f -name 'SKILL.md' | sort\",\n    \"expected_outputs\": \"list of SKILL.md files\",\n    \"validation_method\": \"output_lines > 0\",\n    \"artifact_destination\": \"projects/{project_key}/inventory_skills.txt\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nFix the `long-prompt-orchestrator` to generate **executable plans** that main agent can use without manual translation.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Update Plan Format\nModify the plan generation to include these REQUIRED fields per task:\n- `execution_mode`: \"main\" | \"subagent\" | \"mixed\"\n- `action_type`: \"exec\" | \"python\" | \"skill_invocation\" | \"file_operation\"\n- `action_instructions`: Specific, executable instructions\n- `required_inputs`: List of inputs needed\n- `expected_outputs`: What outputs should be produced\n- `validation_method`: How to validate task completion\n- `recommended_skill_or_role`: Which skill/sub-agent should handle this\n- `artifact_destination`: Where to store outputs\n\n### 2. Ensure Executability\n- Tasks must be specific enough for direct execution\n- No abstract objectives like \"analyze the system\"\n- Instead: \"Run command: find ... | wc -l\"\n- Include concrete validation criteria\n\n### 3. Preserve Architecture\n- Skill remains planner/decomposer only\n- Main agent remains executor/delegator\n- No spawning code added to skill\n- Only plan format improvements\n\n### 4. Testing Requirements\nCreate test that proves:\n- Generated plan is executable by main agent\n- Main can execute/delegate based on plan\n- Tasks produce real artifacts\n- Final synthesis based on real completed tasks\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY\n1. `scripts/orchestrate.py` - Main orchestration logic\n2. `scripts/plan_generator.py` - Plan generation logic\n3. `SKILL.md` - Update documentation to reflect new plan format\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Updated code** with executable plan format\n2. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Old plan (abstract) vs new plan (executable)\n   - Main agent successfully using new plan\n   - Real artifacts produced from plan execution\n3. **Updated documentation** reflecting changes\n4. **Handoff report** with outcome and incidents\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO fake UUIDs or simulated sub-agents\n- NO placeholder artifacts\n- NO manual completion by you\n- REAL execution evidence required\n- REAL artifact creation shown\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`long-prompt-orchestrator` moves from PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL in certification matrix when:\n1. Plans are executable without manual translation\n2. Main agent can use plans directly\n3. Real distributed execution is enabled (when tasks marked for subagents)\n4. Evidence shows real artifact creation from plan execution\n\nProceed with surgical fixes to make plans truly usable."}],"timestamp":1773100969427}}
