AIN_AGENT_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw 16672 Mar  9 17:12 PLAN_FORMAT_SPECIFICATION.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw  7726 Mar  9 17:20 QUICK_START_GUIDE.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw  6603 Mar  9 15:11 RUNTIME_UPGRADE_SUMMARY.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw 11582 Mar  9 16:54 SKILL.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw 15778 Mar  9 14:45 SKILL.md.old_with_spawning\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw 16504 Mar  9 17:28 TROUBLESHOOTING_GUIDE.md\n-rw-rw-r--  1 openclaw openclaw 12960 Mar  9 17:15 VALIDATION_REPORT.md\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 openclaw openclaw  4096 Mar  5 16:21 examples\ndrwxrwxr-x  2 openclaw openclaw  4096 Mar  9 14:49 references\ndrwxrwxr-x  3 openclaw openclaw  4096 Mar  9 17:26 scripts","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773100979203}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9858e34","parentId":"678aba39","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:03.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me read the SKILL.md to understand the current implementation:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_741gKR8TX5mROMn0JBafxdg6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":591,"output":81,"cacheRead":14784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15456,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100979207}}
{"type":"message","id":"20e2e171","parentId":"f9858e34","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:03.684Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_741gKR8TX5mROMn0JBafxdg6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Planner that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into structured plans for main agent execution. Generates task DAGs with dependencies, resource estimates, and execution recommendations. Does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.\ncategory: planning\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n## Purpose\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent tasks, and generate structured execution plans for the main agent. The skill provides comprehensive planning including task dependencies, resource estimates, skill recommendations, and execution strategies. Main agent uses these plans to spawn and coordinate sub-agents.\n\n## CORRECTED ARCHITECTURE (IMPORTANT)\n**This skill ONLY generates plans. It does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.**\n\n### Role Clarification:\n- ✅ **Skill Responsibility**: Planning, decomposition, resource estimation, dependency analysis\n- ✅ **Main Agent Responsibility**: Spawning sub-agents, execution coordination, validation, synthesis\n- ❌ **Skill DOES NOT**: Execute tasks, spawn sub-agents, track execution state, validate outputs\n\n### Key Changes:\n1. **Removed all spawning code** - Skill cannot spawn sub-agents from Python\n2. **Added plan generation** - Outputs structured JSON plans for main agent\n3. **Enhanced task analysis** - Better recommendations for skill/model selection\n4. **Updated documentation** - Clear separation of responsibilities\n\n## When to Use\n- When the main agent receives a prompt that is too long (estimated tokens > 4000)\n- When a task appears complex: expected steps > 5, multi‑file outputs, multi‑agent operations, long tool execution sequences\n- When you need to split a large task into manageable sub‑tasks with dependencies\n- When you need a structured execution plan for distributed workflow\n\n## When NOT to Use\n- For simple, short prompts (estimated tokens < 1000)\n- For tasks that require atomic, non‑decomposable execution\n- When the user explicitly wants a single‑step response\n- When the task is already being handled by another planning/orchestration skill\n- **When you need task execution** (use main agent with generated plan instead)\n\n## Inputs\n- Original prompt (string)\n- Optional configuration (MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, MAX_MINI_TASKS, etc.)\n- Optional checkpoint/task_id for recovery\n\n## Outputs\n- **Structured Plan** (JSON format) containing:\n  - Task definitions with objectives, dependencies, acceptance criteria\n  - Resource estimates (tokens, runtime)\n  - Skill and model recommendations\n  - Dependency graph and execution order\n  - Validation protocol\n  - Distributed execution recommendations\n- Plan file saved to `<workspace>/.taskboards/<plan_id>.json`\n- Human-readable summary (optional)\n\n## Step-by-step Instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Setup\nEnsure the skill directory exists and scripts are executable. Create `.taskboards/` directory if missing.\n\n### Step 1 — Detection\nUse `scripts/decompose.py` to analyze the original prompt:\n- Estimate token count (rough heuristic)\n- Detect complexity heuristics (steps >5, multi‑file outputs, etc.)\n- If prompt is within limits, return simple plan with single task\n\n### Step 2 — Decomposition\nIf decomposition required:\n- Generate a DAG of mini‑tasks each with:\n  - `id`, `objective`, `description`\n  - `inputs`, `outputs`\n  - `dependencies` (list of task ids)\n  - `acceptance_criteria`\n  - `estimated_tokens`, `estimated_runtime`\n  - `complexity_score`\n  - `requires_subagent` (boolean)\n  - `recommended_skill`, `recommended_model` (optional)\n- Ensure total mini‑tasks ≤ MAX_MINI_TASKS (default 20)\n\n### Step 3 — Plan Generation\nUse `scripts/plan_generator.py` to create structured plan:\n- Generate unique `plan_id`\n- Build dependency graph with topological order\n- Calculate resource allocation recommendations\n- Generate validation protocol\n- Add distributed execution recommendations (if using distributed_orchestrate)\n\n### Step 4 — Output\nSave plan to JSON file and return to main agent:\n- Plan saved as `<workspace>/.taskboards/<plan_id>.json`\n- Human-readable summary available (optional)\n- Main agent parses plan and executes accordingly\n\n## Main Agent Integration\n\n### How Main Agent Uses This Skill:\n1. **Invoke skill** with long/complex prompt\n2. **Receive plan** in JSON format\n3. **Parse and validate** plan structure\n4. **Spawn sub-agents** according to plan recommendations\n5. **Coordinate execution** using dependency graph\n6. **Validate outputs** using acceptance criteria\n7. **Synthesize final result**\n\n### Example Main Agent Workflow:\n```python\n# Main agent detects long prompt\nif should_invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator(prompt):\n    # Invoke skill to get plan\n    plan = invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator_skill(prompt)\n    \n    # Validate plan\n    if validate_plan(plan):\n        # Execute plan\n        executor = PlanExecutor(plan)\n        result = executor.execute_plan()\n        \n        # Synthesize final result\n        final_output = synthesize_result(plan, result)\n        return final_output\n```\n\n## File Layout\n```\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md                           (this file)\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py                   (main orchestration - generates plans)\n    decompose.py                     (detect & decompose prompts)\n    plan_generator.py                (generate structured plans)\n    todo.py                          (persistent checklist - for reference)\n    token_budget.py                  (token management - for reference)\n    validate.py                      (validation logic - for reference)\n    recovery.py                      (recovery logic - for reference)\n    learning_emit.py                 (incident emission)\n    context_monitor.py               (monitor context size)\n    context_archive.py               (archive reasoning artifacts)\n    semantic_index_builder.py        (build semantic index of artifacts)\n    semantic_context_search.py       (search semantic index)\n    task_state_manager.py            (persist task state across sessions)\n    session_manager.py               (session lifecycle management)\n    memory_router.py                 (dynamic agent memory routing)\n    context_cleanup.py               (orchestrate context cleanup)\n    distributed_orchestrate.py       (enhanced plans with distribution recommendations)\n  references/\n    design.md                        (design decisions)\n    pattern_keys.md                  (Pattern‑Key definitions)\n    DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md   (decision framework for distribution)\n    TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md        (task assignment guidelines)\n  examples/\n    example_basic.md                 (simple long prompt example)\n    example_complex.md               (complex multi‑file example)\n```\n\n## Plan Format Specification\n\nPlans follow a structured JSON format defined in `PLAN_FORMAT_SPECIFICATION.md`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"plan_id\": \"plan_20260309_1600_a1b2c3d4\",\n  \"original_prompt\": \"truncated prompt...\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-09T16:00:00Z\",\n  \"estimated_total_tokens\": 12000,\n  \"estimated_total_runtime_seconds\": 300,\n  \"global_token_budget\": 16000,\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"task_01_introduction\",\n      \"objective\": \"Write introduction section\",\n      \"description\": \"Detailed description...\",\n      \"inputs\": [],\n      \"outputs\": [\"introduction.md\"],\n      \"dependencies\": [],\n      \"acceptance_criteria\": [\"File exists\", \"Word count >= 250\"],\n      \"estimated_tokens\": 800,\n      \"estimated_runtime_seconds\": 60,\n      \"complexity_score\": 3,\n      \"requires_subagent\": false,\n      \"recommended_skill\": null,\n      \"recommended_model\": null,\n      \"priority\": \"medium\",\n      \"execution_hints\": {\n        \"parallelizable\": true,\n        \"requires_isolation\": false,\n        \"risk_level\": \"low\",\n        \"retry_policy\": \"immediate_2\"\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"dependency_graph\": {\n    \"nodes\": [\"task_01_introduction\"],\n    \"edges\": [],\n    \"topological_order\": [\"task_01_introduction\"]\n  },\n  \"resource_allocation\": {\n    \"max_concurrent_tasks\": 2,\n    \"token_budget_per_phase\": 4000,\n    \"recommended_batch_size\": 1\n  },\n  \"validation_protocol\": {\n    \"pre_execution_checks\": [\"Verify workspace permissions\"],\n    \"post_execution_validation\": [\"Validate acceptance criteria\"],\n    \"final_synthesis_requirements\": [\"Combine outputs\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Distributed Execution Recommendations\n\nFor complex workflows, use `distributed_orchestrate.py` to generate enhanced plans with:\n\n1. **Skill Grouping**: Tasks grouped by recommended skill (Salesforce, web search, etc.)\n2. **Concurrency Analysis**: Recommendations for parallel execution\n3. **Execution Strategy**: Phased approach for optimal resource usage\n4. **Critical Path Identification**: Highlight tasks that impact overall timeline\n\n## Example Usage\n\n### Via CLI:\n```bash\ncd /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n# Generate plan for prompt\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --prompt \"Your long prompt here\"\n\n# Run demos\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo complex\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo upgrade\n\n# Generate enhanced distributed plan\npython3 scripts/distributed_orchestrate.py\n```\n\n### Integration with Main Agent:\nWhen main agent detects a long prompt:\n1. Spawn sub‑agent with this skill\n2. Pass the original prompt as argument\n3. Receive structured plan in JSON format\n4. Use plan to spawn and coordinate sub‑agents\n5. Follow validation protocol for quality assurance\n\n### Manual Plan Examination:\n```bash\n# View generated plan\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/.taskboards/plan_*.json | jq .\n\n# Check task dependencies\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/.taskboards/plan_*.json | jq '.dependency_graph'\n\n# List tasks requiring sub-agents\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/.taskboards/plan_*.json | jq '.tasks[] | select(.requires_subagent == true)'\n```\n\n## Configuration\nEnvironment variables or config file can override:\n- `MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS` (default 4000)\n- `MAX_MINI_TASKS` (default 20)\n- `GLOBAL_TOKEN_BUDGET` (default 16000)\n\n## Quick Validation\nRun the demo to verify the skill works:\n```bash\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\n```\nCheck that:\n- Decomposition result printed\n- Plan generated with tasks\n- Plan saved to JSON file\n- No spawning attempts (correct behavior)\n\n## Important Notes\n\n### What This Skill CAN Do:\n- ✅ Analyze prompt complexity\n- ✅ Decompose into manageable tasks\n- ✅ Generate structured execution plans\n- ✅ Estimate resources (tokens, runtime)\n- ✅ Recommend skills and models\n- ✅ Build dependency graphs\n- ✅ Provide validation protocols\n\n### What This Skill CANNOT Do:\n- ❌ Spawn sub-agents (impossible from Python)\n- ❌ Execute tasks directly\n- ❌ Coordinate distributed execution\n- ❌ Validate task outputs\n- ❌ Track execution state\n- ❌ Synthesize final results\n\n### Migration from Previous Version:\nIf you were using this skill for execution, you must now:\n1. Use the skill to generate plans\n2. Implement plan execution in main agent\n3. Handle spawning and coordination in main agent\n4. Use generated validation protocol for quality control\n\n## References\n- `PLAN_FORMAT_SPECIFICATION.md` - Complete plan format specification\n- `MAIN_AGENT_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md` - Guide for main agent integration\n- `LONG_PROMPT_ORCHESTRATOR_CORRECTED_ARCHITECTURE.md` - Architecture changes documentation"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773100983682}}
