{"type":"message","id":"c6014e44","parentId":"464895b7","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:14:52.172Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_OLy8gG5BFMOnyGVRpRJ4PK4J","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  - `complexity_score`\n  - `requires_subagent` (boolean)\n  - `recommended_skill`, `recommended_model` (optional)\n- Ensure total mini‑tasks ≤ MAX_MINI_TASKS (default 20)\n\n### Step 3 — Plan Generation\nUse `scripts/plan_generator.py` to create structured plan:\n- Generate unique `plan_id`\n- Build dependency graph with topological order\n- Calculate resource allocation recommendations\n- Generate validation protocol\n- Add distributed execution recommendations (if using distributed_orchestrate)\n\n### Step 4 — Output\nSave plan to JSON file and return to main agent:\n- Plan saved as `<workspace>/.taskboards/<plan_id>.json`\n- Human-readable summary available (optional)\n- Main agent parses plan and executes accordingly\n\n## Main Agent Integration\n\n### How Main Agent Uses This Skill:\n1. **Invoke skill** with long/complex prompt\n2. **Receive plan** in JSON format\n3. **Parse and validate** plan structure\n4. **Spawn sub-agents** according to plan recommendations\n5. **Coordinate execution** using dependency graph\n6. **Validate outputs** using acceptance criteria\n7. **Synthesize final result**\n\n### Example Main Agent Workflow:\n```python\n# Main agent detects long prompt\nif should_invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator(prompt):\n    # Invoke skill to get plan\n    plan = invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator_skill(prompt)\n    \n    # Validate plan\n    if validate_plan(plan):\n        # Execute plan\n        executor = PlanExecutor(plan)\n        result = executor.execute_plan()\n        \n        # Synthesize final result\n        final_output = synthesize_result(plan, result)\n        return final_output\n```\n\n## File Layout\n```\n\n[204 more lines in file. Use offset=130 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101692160}}
{"type":"message","id":"3588a8f5","parentId":"c6014e44","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:15:16.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me add a section about the new executable plan format after the \"Main Agent Integration\" section:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_vsqibRmpTzZ1AK847PSQoVW9","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md","oldText":"### Example Main Agent Workflow:\n```python\n# Main agent detects long prompt\nif should_invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator(prompt):\n    # Invoke skill to get plan\n    plan = invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator_skill(prompt)\n    \n    # Validate plan\n    if validate_plan(plan):\n        # Execute plan\n        executor = PlanExecutor(plan)\n        result = executor.execute_plan()\n        \n        # Synthesize final result\n        final_output = synthesize_result(plan, result)\n        return final_output\n```","newText":"### Example Main Agent Workflow:\n```python\n# Main agent detects long prompt\nif should_invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator(prompt):\n    # Invoke skill to get plan\n    plan = invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator_skill(prompt)\n    \n    # Validate plan\n    if validate_plan(plan):\n        # Execute plan\n        executor = PlanExecutor(plan)\n        result = executor.execute_plan()\n        \n        # Synthesize final result\n        final_output = synthesize_result(plan, result)\n        return final_output\n```\n\n## New Executable Plan Format (Updated 2026-03-10)\n\nThe skill now generates **executable plans** with these key improvements:\n\n### 1. Executable Task Instructions\n- **Old format**: Abstract objectives like \"Analyze the system\"\n- **New format**: Specific, executable instructions like \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills -type f -name 'SKILL.md' | sort\"\n\n### 2. Required Fields for Direct Execution\nEach task now includes:\n- `execution_mode`: \"main\" | \"subagent\" | \"mixed\" (who should execute)\n- `action_type`: \"exec\" | \"python\" | \"skill_invocation\" | \"file_operation\" (type of action)\n- `action_instructions`: Specific, executable instructions\n- `validation_method`: How to validate task completion\n- `artifact_destination`: Where to store outputs\n- `recommended_skill_or_role`: Which skill/sub-agent should handle this\n\n### 3. Benefits for Main Agent\n- **No manual translation needed**: Main agent can execute tasks directly\n- **Clear execution decisions**: Based on `execution_mode` field\n- **Built-in validation**: Each task has `validation_method`\n- **Artifact management**: Outputs stored at `artifact_destination`\n- **Distributed execution**: Tasks marked for subagents enable parallel execution\n\n### 4. Example Task Comparison\n**Old (abstract):**\n```json\n{\n  \"task_id\": \"task_01\",\n  \"objective\": \"Which skills actually work and produce real results.\",\n  \"description\": \"Which skills actually work and produce real results.\"\n}\n```\n\n**New (executable):**\n```json\n{\n  \"task_id\": \"task_01\",\n  \"objective\": \"Inventory all skills in workspace\",\n  \"description\": \"List all available skills with their status and dependencies\",\n  \"execution_mode\": \"main\",\n  \"action_type\": \"exec\",\n  \"action_instructions\": \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills -type f -name 'SKILL.md' | sort\",\n  \"validation_method\": \"output_lines > 0\",\n  \"artifact_destination\": \"projects/{project_key}/inventory_skills.txt\"\n}\n```"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":424,"output":835,"cacheRead":54912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56171,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101692170}}
